        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Meanwhile, <a href="https://deepmind.com/research/publications/mastering-game-go-deep-neural-networks-tree-search/" target="_self">AlphaGo</a> defeated one of the best human players at Go ‚Äî an extraordinary achievement in a game dominated by humans for two decades after machines first conquered chess. Many masters could not fathom how it would be possible for a machine to grasp the full nuance and complexity of this ancient Chinese war strategy game, with its 10¬π‚Å∑‚Å∞ possible board positions (there are only <a href="http://www.slate.com/articles/technology/technology/2016/03/google_s_alphago_defeated_go_champion_lee_sedol_ken_jennings_explains_what.html" target="_self">10‚Å∏‚Å∞atoms in the universe</a>).</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
